  canonical="/gepco-bill/"

  introContent={`
    <p>Gujranwala Electric Power Company (GEPCO) supplies electricity to over 3.9 million consumers across six districts of Punjab: <strong>Gujranwala</strong>, <strong>Sialkot</strong>, <strong>Gujrat</strong>, <strong>Hafizabad</strong>, <strong>Narowal</strong>, and <strong>Mandi Bahauddin</strong>. Established in 1998 from WAPDA's Central Punjab zone, GEPCO serves one of Pakistan's most industrially productive regions — home to the surgical instruments capital of Asia (Sialkot), Pakistan's largest steel market, and one of the country's most dense small-industry corridors.</p>
    <p>GEPCO's service territory includes <strong>Gujranwala city</strong> — Pakistan's fifth-largest city and an industrial powerhouse — along with the entire districts of Sialkot (including Daska and Sambrial), Gujrat (including Kharian and Lalamusa), Hafizabad, Narowal (including Shakargarh), and Mandi Bahauddin. The Sialkot industrial cluster, with its surgical, sports goods, and leather exports, makes GEPCO a critical supplier of industrial electricity in Pakistan.</p>
    <p>To check your GEPCO bill online, enter your <strong>14-digit GEPCO reference number</strong> in the bill checker above. GEPCO also offers an <strong>SMS service via 8118</strong> — send your 14-digit reference number to 8118 for instant bill and meter details by SMS. Alternatively, use your <strong>7-digit or 10-digit Consumer ID</strong> (click the Customer ID tab) to retrieve your bill.</p>
    <p>GEPCO has been progressive in adopting smart meters and net metering. Industrial and commercial consumers in Gujranwala and Sialkot use GEPCO's online systems extensively. GEPCO's billing cycle runs monthly, with bills available on the PITC server by the 20th to 25th of each month.</p>
    <p>PakistanBill.online is <strong>Pakistan's only platform</strong> covering all 19 utility providers. Alongside this checker, you can also check: <a href="/lesco-bill/">LESCO bill</a> | <a href="/fesco-bill/">FESCO bill</a> | <a href="/iesco-bill/">IESCO bill</a> | <a href="/sngpl-bill/">SNGPL gas bill</a>. Use our free <a href="/electricity-bill-calculator/">electricity bill calculator</a> to estimate charges before your bill arrives, or visit our <a href="/dashboard/">universal bill dashboard</a> to check multiple bills without switching pages. Also see: <a href="/blog/gepco-reference-number/">How to find your GEPCO reference number</a> — and our complete <a href="/gujranwala/">Gujranwala utility bills guide</a>.</p>
  `}

  howToSteps={[
    "Locate your 14-digit GEPCO reference number — printed in bold at the top of your GEPCO electricity bill, on the right side near your consumer details.",
    "Go to the bill checker tool at the top of this page. The Reference Number tab is selected by default.",
    "Enter your 14-digit GEPCO reference number in the input field. Numbers only — no spaces or dashes.",
    "Click Check Bill. The tool connects to the official PITC server (bill.pitc.com.pk/gepcobill) and fetches your bill.",
    "Your complete GEPCO bill appears in 3 to 5 seconds — showing amount due, due date, units consumed, meter readings, and all charges.",
    "Click Download PDF to save your bill as PDF, or click Print to get a paper duplicate copy immediately."
  ]}

  billReadingTips={[
    "Your GEPCO reference number (14 digits) is your permanent account ID. Save it in your phone — you need it every month to check your bill online without hunting for a paper copy.",
    "GEPCO's SMS service via 8118 is unique to GEPCO. Send your 14-digit reference number to 8118 for bill amount, due date, and meter reading details by SMS — different from the 8334 service used by other DISCOs.",
    "The Category field shows your tariff classification. D-Protected means subsidized rates. D-Unprotected means full commercial slab rates. Industrial consumers see I-1, I-2, or I-3 depending on voltage and demand.",
    "Sialkot and Gujranwala industrial consumers should check their Maximum Demand (MD) reading on the bill. MD charges apply when consumption exceeds sanctioned load — a major driver of high industrial bills.",
    "If your bill shows Estimated consumption, GEPCO's meter reader could not access your premises. Request an actual reading immediately — estimated bills often cause surprise catch-up bills the following month.",
    "Net metering consumers should verify that exported units are correctly credited on the bill. GEPCO's net metering reconciliation runs quarterly — check your yearly settlement carefully.",
  ]}

  savingTips={[
    "Sialkot and Gujranwala industrial units: shift production schedules to avoid GEPCO peak hours (6:30–10:30 PM summer). Running heavy machinery during off-peak hours reduces demand charges significantly for bulk consumers.",
    "Gujranwala residential consumers: use inverter ACs and LED lighting to stay under the 200-unit Protected threshold. Gujranwala's moderate climate (cooler than Multan) means most households can achieve this with basic efficiency measures.",
    "Apply for GEPCO net metering. Sialkot's export-earning industries and Gujranwala's manufacturing units are ideal candidates for rooftop solar. Net metering can reduce industrial electricity costs by 40–60%.",
    "Use programmable timers on water motors and electric geysers. Set them to run between 2 PM and 5 PM — off-peak, low-demand hours — and program them off before peak hours begin at 6:30 PM.",
    "Compare your GEPCO bill month-over-month using our tool. A sudden spike in consumption without change in appliance usage usually indicates a meter fault — request a free meter inspection within 7 days of billing.",
    "Switch all home and factory lighting to LED. A typical Gujranwala factory replacing 100 fluorescent tube lights (40W each) with LED tubes (20W each) saves 60 units per 8-hour working day — approximately 1,500 units per month.",
  ]}

  complaintProcess={[
    "Call GEPCO helpline 118 or 055-9200516 with your 14-digit reference number. State the complaint clearly — overbilling, wrong category, TP penalty, or meter fault.",
    "Get a Complaint Registration Number (CRN) from the GEPCO agent. Without this, your complaint has no official record. If the agent refuses, escalate to the GEPCO subdivision officer directly.",
    "Visit your nearest GEPCO sub-division office in Gujranwala, Sialkot, Gujrat, Hafizabad, Narowal, or Mandi Bahauddin for billing disputes that require document review.",
    "GEPCO must resolve billing complaints within 14 working days under NEPRA regulations. If unresolved, call NEPRA at 0800-63000 (toll-free) to file a regulatory complaint.",
    "Escalate to the Federal Ombudsman (Wafaqi Mohtasib) at mohtasib.gov.pk for complaints NEPRA also fails to resolve — this is a legally binding free escalation route.",
  ]}

  smsService="Send your 14-digit GEPCO reference number as an SMS to 8118. GEPCO replies with your bill amount, due date, and meter reading details. Note: GEPCO uses 8118, not 8334 like other DISCOs."

