  faqs={[
    { question: "How do I check my GEPCO bill online in March 2026?", answer: "Enter your 14-digit GEPCO reference number in the bill checker at the top of this page and click Check Bill. Your complete GEPCO electricity bill appears in seconds — showing amount due, due date, units consumed, and all surcharges. Free, no login required, works 24/7." },
    { question: "What is GEPCO's SMS service number?", answer: "GEPCO's SMS service uses 8118 — not 8334 like other DISCOs. Send your 14-digit GEPCO reference number as an SMS to 8118. GEPCO replies with your current bill amount, due date, and meter reading details. This is the only DISCO with a dedicated SMS shortcode for bill and meter data combined." },
    { question: "How do I check my GEPCO bill for Sialkot?", answer: "Sialkot is within GEPCO's service area. Enter your 14-digit GEPCO reference number in the bill checker above — the same tool works for all GEPCO districts including Sialkot, Daska, Sambrial, and Pasrur. Sialkot reference numbers have the same 14-digit format as all other GEPCO connections." },
    { question: "How do I check my GEPCO bill for Gujrat?", answer: "Gujrat district is fully covered by GEPCO. Enter your 14-digit reference number in the checker above. Gujrat, Kharian, Lalamusa, and Sara-e-Alamgir all fall under GEPCO. Your bill will load from the PITC server in 3 to 5 seconds." },
    { question: "How do I download my GEPCO duplicate bill?", answer: "After your bill loads in the checker, click Download PDF. Select Save as PDF in the browser print dialog and click Save. Your GEPCO duplicate bill downloads as a PDF instantly — ready to share on WhatsApp or present at a JazzCash shop for payment." },
    { question: "How do I pay my GEPCO bill online?", answer: "Pay through JazzCash, Easypaisa, or any bank mobile app. Open the app, go to Bill Payments, select Electricity, choose GEPCO, enter your 14-digit reference number, verify the amount, and confirm. Payment reflects on the GEPCO system within 2 to 4 hours." },
    { question: "What is GEPCO's grace period for bill payment?", answer: "GEPCO gives 7 days after the due date to pay without a late payment surcharge. After this grace period, a 10% surcharge applies to the full unpaid amount. Always pay on or before your due date to avoid this penalty." },
    { question: "How do I apply for GEPCO net metering?", answer: "Visit gepco.com.pk and navigate to the net metering section, or visit the nearest GEPCO division office. You need a NEPRA-licensed solar installer, technical drawings of your solar system, and a load approval letter. GEPCO installs a bidirectional meter. Surplus solar units exported to the grid credit your monthly bill at the approved buyback rate." },
    { question: "Which districts does GEPCO serve?", answer: "GEPCO covers six districts of Punjab: Gujranwala, Sialkot, Gujrat, Hafizabad, Narowal, and Mandi Bahauddin. The company serves 3.9 million consumers across this region, including major cities Gujranwala (Pakistan's fifth largest city) and Sialkot (the surgical instruments and sports goods export capital)." },
    { question: "How do I file a billing complaint with GEPCO?", answer: "Call GEPCO helpline 118 or 055-9200516 with your reference number. Get a Complaint Registration Number (CRN). GEPCO must resolve within 14 working days under NEPRA regulations. If unresolved, call NEPRA at 0800-63000. For industrial billing disputes in Sialkot or Gujranwala, visit the GEPCO commercial billing division with your bill and CNIC." },
  ]}

